body:
According to the [documentation](https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_58_0/libs/filesystem/doc/reference.html#copy_file), the return type is void, but throws an error if it cannot copy.
So try/catch can be used instead.

```suggestion
    try
    {
        fs::copy_file(backup_file, wallet_file, fs::copy_option::fail_if_exists);
    } catch (const boost::filesystem::filesystem_error& e)
    {
        throw JSONRPCError(RPC_MISC_ERROR, "Unable to copy backup file.");
    }
```

